# Gameplay Standards

Canonical: `Documents/01_Game_Design/GameplayDesignBible.md` (PE-016).

## Identity

Psychological survival horror — investigation, exploration, grounded facility puzzles. Not an action shooter, stealth combat arena, or RPG. Progression via knowledge, access, and systems literacy.

## Loop

Explore → Observe → Collect → Solve → World Response → Survive (presence) → Proceed.

## Rules

- Align missions with the Gameplay Design Bible; conflicts require an ADR before implement.
- Reuse Interaction, Inventory, Objectives, Power, Puzzle (PE-015), Witness presence patterns.
- Do not introduce combat, chase AI, or new core mechanics unless the approved brief **and** ADR allow it.
- Witness pressures attention; never replaces solvable puzzle/ops logic.
- Prefer one teaching beat per mission (e.g. fuse aux vs fuel/generator main).
- Generator World Response stays independent of puzzle `NotifyPuzzlePowerResponse`.

## Anti-patterns

- Parallel frameworks (second inventory / power / objective system)
- Glyph pads / arbitrary sequences without facility realism
- Feature demos disguised as production slices
- Silent divergence from the bible
